text:
Some insider rrats, believe them or not idgaf. I was on a single call during Reflect production where they were workshopping an early draft, and that's it. I think I said one whole sentence, and there were maybe 8-12 people on the call. We all had to literally call in old-school style, so no discord.

>Gura was "in character" at all times as far as her vo*ce goes. Whether that's part of her creative process or Cover policy about avoiding "real vo*ce" leaks I have no idea.
>She asked a LOT of questions about the process and seemed actually really involved. In my experience, that's rare for a singer whose song is being written by committee.
>An early draft had a line that started "Ever since I was just a kid" got axed because her manager was worried "since I was" sounded too much like "*", no joke. The final draft had that section completely different so it didn't matter anyway, but I thought that was funny considering they literally let her do Country Roads.
>They kept focusing on it being an "opener", meaning a high energy track that could kick off a show in the eventuality of a HoloEN online concert. From what it sounds like, they would want to open and close with Gura-centric songs since she's the biggest EN crowd draw.

text:
Glad you wrote down to get ytcFilter! It's a great tool to filter out translations (filter out messages for [en], (trans), en: ) and especially for catching when other Hololive girls say something. 
You can look up some filters that people use for Vtubers and Google would probably redirect you to a reddit post about common filters people use. It's also customizable to per channel like filtering out only Translator X for Pekora's videos and then Translator Y for Haachama's videos or you can set global filters that work for all channels like mod and owner filtering. 

It's great to use as a transcript (if there's a live translator) when you're doing other stuff and can't listen in or you can mute the stream and just read the translation for what is going on. You can also popout the ytcFilter chat box if you want. The dev is always up for feedback and bug fixes as well. 

Mentioned it in the SC but Youtube Vanced is great to bypass ads and playing youtube in the background on your phone. It's not in the app store and you have to find the file online to download it. 

Hope you recommend it to the other Hololive members too! :_GuYum:

text:
Unbeatable's aesthetic is really cool, but boy it is visually noisy even for rhythm game standards. Fortunate the devs are still active though. It was awesome seeing how you went from 12ms delay to 1ms on a couple songs too. That is insanely fast :_GuraAA:

You also might not need a splitter. It sounded like your sponsorship got you a second capture card that you have to figure out. If it has one Input and two Outputs, you can use that instead of a splitter. One goes to your PC while the other goes to your TV.
